the taste, which made the dish not as memorable or satisfying as the Braised Short Rib. It was also an appetizer-more expensive than the Braised Short Rib!\n\nService was great by the way, and our waiter convinced us to try the $9 Pineapple Carpaccio, a light, fruity dessert with a unique presentation consisting of dry ice and vapor (highly recommended for the novelty of the dessert!).\n\nNOTE: Although the Beef Wellington was a bit disappointing, there was only one downside of the meal: bottled water. When asked if we wanted house or bottled water, I absentmindedly chose bottled water, only to find at the end of the meal that bottled water costs $8 (EIGHT DOLLARS!!!) per bottle. C'mon Gordon, just keep it simple and only offer free house water, which is probably the same as the bottled water anyway. This isn't Europe.\n\nUltimately, I still recommend checking out Hell's Kitchen, not just for the great food, but also just for a fun, satisfying experience at one of the best-in-the-world celebrity chef's restaurants!","date":"2018-09-03 06:37:14"}
