{"review_id":"uyTOgS8gIWVlxqkfGa1biw","user_id":"HQlvsUqVhtJDH0ASBzaLsA","business_id":"vHz2RLtfUMVRPFmd7VBEHA","stars":5.0,"useful":0,"funny":0,"cool":0,"text":"I'm mainly going to talk about the food here. Everything else was business as usual. Nothing out of the ordinary, and nothing mind blowing either. I have my overall review down below if you want to skip all the details. Here we go:\n\nI ordered three appetizers: scallops, \"wagyu\" meatballs, and tuna tartare. \n\nThe tartare was as perfect of a dish as you can get: a little sweet, a little spice, a little crunch. I like the taro chips it was served with. Very clean and fresh dish. Mouth watering. \n\nI loved ALMOST everything about the scallops too. Perfect sear, super flavorful celeriac purée, and nice clean garnishes like pickled apples. My single issue with the dish is that you are served five HALVED scallops. Oy vay. Why oh why are you cutting these delicate, beautiful pillows of the sea in half? Naturally, they were a bit over cooked. But again, the flavor was on point. No doubt about that. \n\nAnd finally we have the \"wagyu\" meatballs. So here we have meatballs: a poor man's food, traditionally made with cheaper cuts of meat. In my opinion, using something as special as wagyu beef in such a dish is preposterous, over indulgent and almost sacrilegious. The exquisite flavor of such a special piece of meat is lost in all the spices and sauce and cheese that are also in there. Wagyu should take center stage of any dish where it's an ingredient. It should be cooked simply, not ground into meatballs and braised in a spicy, rich tomato sauce. That being said, the flavor was...well they were meatballs and they tasted like meatballs. Delicious, but nothing special...and nothing a beautiful Italian Nonna couldn't make better. \n\nOVERALL:\nAtmosphere - sleek, modern, trendy, beautifully designed\n\nStaff - friendly, knowledgeable and eager to please\n\nDrinks - great wine list and beautifully crafted cocktails using fresh squeezed juice to order. You can definitely notice the difference. \n\nFood - flavor and seasoning spot on. For more details, see above. \n\nFinal thoughts - for a restaurant that's been open less than a month, bravo! Plating and menu descriptions need a little work. I was definitely more impressed than I thought I would be. Kudos to the chef and BOH and FOH teams for a job well done! Congrats on a successful opening!\n\n*****UPDATE*****\n\nWent back and this time sat at a table. Britney, our server, was a delight. She had extensive knowledge of the menu and was available, but not overbearing. Louie, the GM, sat with us for us while. Down to earth and just an overall a lovely man. Manny, the AGM, took us to our table and explained the concept a little to us. He's got an upbeat attitude and you can tell he really believes in the place.  We felt very taken care of by everyone this time which made our experience that much better.","date":"2018-05-13 16:46:30"}
