hat was amazing.\n\nMy meal consisted of the lobster risotto, filet mignon, & mac n cheese.  Like I said, I'm not a seafood person, but that lobster was delish!  The risotto  was rich and creamy and the lobster was not what I expected.  It didn't have a super fishy taste and the texture was smooth and easy to chew.  I'm sure this is what good lobster tastes like LOL!  I don't think anything will every compare to this dish.  I did give some to hubby, but I ate most of that dish by myself.  The filet was ok, I've had better, but it's not a deal breaker at all.  The mac n cheese was warm, not super hot, but tasted good.  The gouda and crispy prosciutto made the dish.  \n\nHell's Kitchen definitely lived up to our expectations and we can't wait to go back.  Cheers!","date":"2018-08-08 17:12:11"}
