{"review_id":"kPkKqTA79RDz3C0jqca3Lw","user_id":"ONNF30FbGDhw1T3vA3C5fw","business_id":"vHz2RLtfUMVRPFmd7VBEHA","stars":4.0,"useful":14,"funny":4,"cool":9,"text":"It's hard to visit The Strip these days without Gordon Ramsey being in your face somewhere.  In this case, it was right in front of our resort at Caesar's Palace at Hell's Kitchen (albeit separated by a ramp built for a motorcycle jump over the resorts' kitchen).  Be sure to book WEEKS ahead or you won't get your reservation.\n\nThe theme of the restaurant has heavy doses of the TV show which inspires the name.  The fiery statue out front is even inspired by the graphics for the show.  But if you're not a show viewer (which I'm not) you won't be distracted by the theme -- the show is there on monitors in the dining area, but large windows allow you to see the resort's sculptures and the curved shape of the restaurant feels roomy.  \n\nThe menu has so much to explore and it is worth ordering to share and enjoy.  I HIGHLY recommend Scampi Prawn Flambe, if for nothing else but the theater of cooking on your table (see the video).  But the flavor of the shrimp with the white wine sauce is great on the palate.  I had the Crispy Skin Salmon but only because my dinner partner had the Beef Wellington which I was going to try come Hell('s Kitchen) or high water.  The salmon was creamy, buttery and flavorful -- but lacking a small kick of salt or spice. The skin was perfectly done.  The bites of Beef Wellington I was allowed to try were perfectly done and the pastry was delicious.  The Sticky Toffee Pudding was the obligatory finish and was good but a finish that begged for an espresso or Port to accompany it.\n\nService was tremendous.\n\nThis is the latest \"must-try\" high-end restaurant in Las Vegas.  But with so many other restaurants at the same price point and navigation around The Strip so difficult, I wouldn't recommend Hell's Kitchen as a destination point unless you're a huge fan of Ramsey or just want to try a very nicely done Beef Wellington.  But, if you're in the area, DO IT.","date":"2018-07-15 08:20:22"}
