asteless.  The filet was okay, but I have had much better.  It also was flavorless.  The duxelle was also just a boring, flavorless mushroom paste.  The pastry fell off as soon as you cut into it.  The potato puree was also just a baby food version of mashed potatoes with no taste, except, you guessed it...potato.  The root vegetables consisted of 2 carrot balls and 2 parsnip balls that were under cooked and had a slight butter flavor, but nothing more.  The demi glace was a saving grace as it helped amp up the flavor slightly.\n\nDessert was the Sticky Toffee Pudding with Speculoos ice cream.  This was good, but way too sweet.  When you need to use ice cream to cut the sweetness, it's a problem.  The cake itself was moist and fine.  The sauce was overwhelmingly sweet.\n\nAll in all.  The service was great, the decor was fun, the experience was good.  The food was lacking.  You will spend about $100-$200 per person depending on drinks and appetizers.  I would recommend just going to the bar for drinks and spending that money on better food elsewhere.  Gordon Ramsay should be ashamed of this place.  He may need someone to come in and help with this kitchen nightmare.","date":"2018-10-21 14:59:05"}
