n the food initially because there is always that hype factor when you see something on tv versus actual experience.  Boy was I wrong.  Food looked amd tasted exactly how I imagined.  Amazing!! The pan seared scallops were cooked and seasoned perfectly, nice and seared on the outside and soft on the inside.  The lobster in the rosotto was so sweet and suculent it was poached with a lot of heart and effort.  The beef wellington was just wow.  Flaky outer pastry puff surrounding the mushroom filling that wraps around a high end piece of meat.  Its either beef tenderloin or filet mignon, probably mignon, but either way it was tender and soft and cuts like a hit knife on butter.  Melts in your mouth texture.  I recommend if you and whoever you go with if you guys are not super big eaters to get 1 beeft wellington to share so you can order more items.  My wife and I both each had one beef wellington and it was quite filling.  The caramel toffee cake ended the evening and our experience at Hells Kitchen wanting more.  \n\nI highly recommend this restaurant for any occassion, but especially special ones like a birthday or anniversary.","date":"2018-11-11 17:28:37"}
