{"review_id":"fAW-ltuB8NM4IMJqU-c5Sg","user_id":"-EEAtjQn5KSZFzhGpDBNfQ","business_id":"vHz2RLtfUMVRPFmd7VBEHA","stars":3.0,"useful":1,"funny":0,"cool":1,"text":"We decided to go to Hell's Kitchen to celebrate our anniversary and a friends birthday.  We are all fans of Gordon Ramsay and couldn't wait to try the restaurant, plus as an added bonus, we saw Chef Michelle, last seasons winner, was there and we thought it would be fun to meet her.  I did mention when I made the reservations that we were celebrating an anniversary and a birthday.\n\nWhen you first walk in you are greeted by a friendly hostess who wished us a Happy Anniversary and a Happy Birthday.  While we waited for our table, we looked over all the pictures of the Hell's Kitchen season winners.  Some chefs we remembered, some we didn't. \n\nWe were seated pretty quickly and loved the décor.  The kitchen looks just like it does on TV, half blue, half red, the chefs got together at one point and did a little scene, it was a lot of fun to watch.  The ceiling lights were pitchforks and added to the whole effect.  They had 2 TV's on, one was showing scenes from Hell's Kitchen, the other was showing sports.  I'm not sure why they had sports on, we were there to immerse ourselves in the Hell's Kitchen experience, not have a sports program blaring at you.  The restaurant was also very loud, and I mean very, very loud.  The tables aren't that big but we had a hard time hearing each other and our waiter.\n\nWhen we were handed our menus, I opened mine and a few crumbs fell out and there was food stuck to the menu, yuck!  I told my waiter what happened and asked for a new menu.  That seemed to fluster him, he did apologize and brought me a new menu, but he never came back to our table again, I'm not sure why.\n\nEveryone decided to order the pre fixe dinner since that's what Gordon Ramsay is famous for and we couldn't wait to try it.\n\nWhen the scallops arrived, they looked delicious and the plating was stunning.  My first bite let me know it was as delicious as it looked.  The sweet corn puree was tasty and the scallops were cooked perfectly.  There were 2 problems though, the first is they were luke warm when they arrived and cold by the time I got to the last one, the second was everyone found shells in their scallops.  My husband had one so large he had to discreetly spit it out.\n\nThe next course was the beef wellington.  That too looked incredible when it came out.  The puff pastry was crisp and the beef melted in your mouth.  The potatoes and veggies it came with were bland, we looked around for salt and pepper shakers and didn't see any, we assumed it is because Chef Ramsay is big on having food seasoned properly before it leaves the kitchen, they missed the mark on that.\n\nLastly came the sticky toffee pudding.  Let me just say at this point no one is sure how we're going to eat dessert, but when it arrived, it looked and smelled delicious.  It was warm, gooey and tasted like an ultra moist spice cake, only better!  The speculoos ice cream it came with went perfectly with the pudding.  Unfortunately at this point, we were too full to finish it.\n\nOne thing I had noticed reading the reviews, people who were celebrating special events were offered a free dessert, because we ordered off the pre fixe menu, that wasn't possible, it would have been nice to have been offered a glass of wine instead.\n\nAs we were eating dinner, we noticed Chef Michelle greeting different tables and taking pictures.  She had gone back in the kitchen when we were getting ready to leave and we asked our waiter if she could take a picture with us.  When she came to the table she was defensive and short with us.  We started to say we were fans and had watched her last year, but she didn't seem interested and asked if we had a problem or complaint?  We were taken aback and became tongue tied.  I'm not sure what our waiter told her, we didn't complain to him about the scallops or the unseasoned vegetables, so I'm not sure why she thought there was a problem.  Needless to say, we did get our picture taken with her, but it was extremely awkward.  So much so that we cancelled our reservations we had previously made at Ramsays Grill.  If a customer has a complaint, coming at them like that won't make things better.\n\nWe're still big fans of Gordon Ramsay and we are extremely glad we ate at Hell's Kitchen.  The food was truly delicious and it was a once in a lifetime experience for us, although for what it cost, I would rather have had a quieter atmosphere and a much better experience with the back of house staff.","date":"2018-10-26 19:56:32"}
