{"review_id":"AbYn9ZhYoQ3BVvIOuMzPsg","user_id":"BL5LpvgOQs5k7-KBVbzamA","business_id":"vHz2RLtfUMVRPFmd7VBEHA","stars":5.0,"useful":7,"funny":3,"cool":9,"text":"As if Hell's Kitchen needs yet another 5 star review.. But to be brutally honest, our meal here was probably one of the best meals I've ever had so I just have to leave my two cents. Located outside of Cesar's Palace, you'll find that Hell's Kitchen is quite large and elegant. The decor is simple, modern, and beautifully designed. The open kitchen seems to be the main attraction where you can see the chefs carefully crafting and cooking. \n\nFrom appetizer to dessert, everything we had was delicious. For starter, we were given a small watermelon appetizer which was topped with goat cheese and black pepper. The mac and cheese featured smoked gouda and prosciutto. The topping with bread crumbs added an excellent texture. \n\nWe ordered the fixed menu to get the most bang for or buck, which included an appetizer (scallops or Cesar salad), the famous beef wellington, and a dessert (toffee cake with cookie butter icecream). The scallops were cooked perfectly and the corn puree was very light. The beef wellington was cooked to a medium rare. SO TENDER. SO SOFT. The outer breading was delicious- buttery and flakey! The toffee cake was outstanding. The portion size was quite large so it could easily be shared between 2-3 people. The cake itself was so moist, spongey, and buttery. Each bite was heaven. The toffee flavor wasn't as prominent as I thought it would be. It tasted more like a butter cake... and if you're in the city of Sin, this feels no less sinful. The cold icecream paired well with its warmth. I am SO glad we order the fix menu and got to try out all of the dishes. \n\nWith all the food, we left uncomfortably full. I can't remember the last time I've eaten that much food. Despite the crazy steep prices on the menu, all of the food was crafted to perfection and the experience was amazing. Our waitress Sandra answered all our questions and made suggestions. She was really friendly and checked on us frequently. The price for 1 side, 1 entree, 2 alcoholic drinks, and one prefixed menu course added up to about $206 for the both of us. It was truly a once in a lifetime experience so the value was definitely worth it. The portion sizes are surprisingly large. Both of our entrees was more than enough food for us plus the side dish. Presentation could not have been better. \n\nHell's Kitchen is a MUST if you are a Gordon Ramsey fan or even if you're looking for an elegant dinner experience in Las Vegas. Definitely try the beef wellington- you won't regret it!","date":"2018-09-15 23:59:56"}
