d who doesn't like a nice cheese crisp?\n\nBeef Wellington w\/ potato puree, glazed root vegetables, red wine demi-glace:\nExcellent! The beef was pretty spot-on for medium rare. The inside had a nice pink center, whereas the outer layers were cooked well. It had a good amount of springiness to it, while it was wrapped in buttery, flaky pastry. Plus, the red wine demi-glace was not too overpowering.\nSome more vegetables would have been nice since there was only 1 carrot and 1 radish on the plate. And... isn't potato puree pretty much just mashed potato?\n\nSticky Toffee Pudding w\/ speculoos ice cream:\nGood! If you plan to order this, it may be best to share it. This is yet another hefty portion. Luckily for me, my friend did a very good job eating her fair share, since I was starting to feel the weight of all the food. Plus the sticky toffee pudding was a little too sweet for me. To me, it most resembles a heavy cake drenched in syrup. The speculoos ice cream was ok, but the coldness helped to break up the heavy sweetness.\n\nIf I had room for one more dish, I probably would have ordered the scallops. In short, HK serves quality classic dishes, and the service was very good too.","date":"2018-10-31 09:44:06"}
