 eaten. Also the beef wellington is great. The beef super tender surrounded by mushroom paste, and wrapped in pastry. Really exceptional. Also if you are here you should get a drink as they have some excellent choices. I got the Meet your maker and it was excellent. When it comes time for dessert you basically have one choice which will be getting the sticky toffee pudding with speculoos ice cream. Overall very impressive. Having been to the other locations in vegas that Gordon runs this is a hare better in facility and presentation. Some of the menu items you could get at the pub, or steakhouse, but there is literally only one Hells Kitchen. It has set a high dining mark that might take a while to be toppled in my book.","date":"2018-07-05 19:47:22"}
