st like how my boyfriend likes it. He had no complaints and would order again.\n\nDinner menu (scallops, beef wellington, sticky toffee pudding): 4\/5\nI thought the scallops were good, nice and soft. The beef Wellington for me was a salty and I couldn't really pinpoint it. I think it was the puff pastry and the additional salt they put but it just tasted really salty. The filet mignon itself was soft and nicely finished. I really loved the sticky toffee pudding. They gave such a huge dessert portion to that I was physically struggling to finish it - and trust me my brain was trying to hold me back but my stomach was begging for more. It was sweet but not the kind that you were like \"ugh\". My only gripe is I wish I had more ice cream to go with it. I didn't finish because I ran out of ice cream and they pair so well together.\n\nOverall = 4\/5\nIt was a nice place to celebrate my boyfriend's birthday. The drinks were great as well as the dessert. My boyfriend liked the beef Wellington, I am willing to give it another go but I am tempted to try something else (as shocking as that sounds). The ambiance itself is very energetic which reminds me of Vegas in general which is good and bad for some.\n\nHint = get a reservation to avoid waiting in line. Also get the prefixe menu and you can't go wrong.","date":"2018-11-10 00:25:53"}
